To the earlier point about the commanders being very specific,  I think that's the new normal for the commander product. For Brawl to survive, it needs broad commanders that can do everything in a narrow card pool in which they may be the only available option for a given color combo.
Which means you're getting broad commanders in every new standard set, leaving the more focused stuff for your commanders, battlebonds, and moderns horizons.

I’m actually more concerned about the niche-ness of the new cards in the 99 than I am about the commanders. On the one hand, niche cards are ideal because it means we don’t have teferi’s protection cards in limited supply. On the other hand, it forces the sexy cards to be reprints, rather than new all-star original cards. So then when the only new card people want is a commander and a treasure goblin, and the reprint value is middling at best, the product paints itself into an awkward corner. 

Not gonna pretend I have the right answer here, but ubiquity of commanders isn’t my worry so much as how they thread the needle with new cards in the 99

The goodstuff factor is why I don't like to build more than two colors. Mono-g I always wanna run Sylvan Library, Beast Within and Heroic Intervention. Add red I wanna run Chaos Warp, Blasphemous Act, Wheel of Fortune, Hull Breach, Rhythm of the Wild, Hull Breach, etc. Add white I wanna run Council's Judgment, Swords, Path, Smothering Tithe, Generous Gift, Wear//Tear, Council's Judgment, Mirari's Wake, Austere, etc. At three colors the amount of just valuable good cards is so high it's hard to leave room for anything else.
